---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Ranking Every Halo Wars 2 Leader - 2026 Edition";
const description = "Annual leader tier list for 2026. A subjective ranking of all Halo Wars 2 leaders from S-tier powerhouses like Atriox and Colony to the situational picks.";
const category = "Reviews";
const publishedDate = "February 2, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-02";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "/content/blog/reviews-placeholder.svg";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  tags={tags}
  youtubeId="tNC5_W3aPQY"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Annual leader ranking for 2026. This is completely subjective based on personal opinions and play styles in Halo Wars 2.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">S Tier (The Best)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Atriox</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the most fun leader wheels</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Great as a base leader</strong> (no DLC required)</li>
    <li>Really good with Super Turtles</li>
    <li>Hero is really strong, really easy to vet up</li>
    <li>Quite dangerous, particularly with spamming cringe air as it gets later into the game</li>
    <li>No liability with his hero</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Colony</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Not only one of the most fun leaders to play, but some of the most creative ways to play</li>
    <li>Can rush with Goliaths or have a hero rush with skitters attached to units (especially Reavers)</li>
    <li>Symbiotes constantly healing with Combat Repair</li>
    <li>Wide variety of unit compositions - not limited to one style</li>
    <li>Can turtle or rush effectively</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Johnson</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">King of Super Turtling</strong></li>
    <li>Johnson hero with Y ability that creates a heal</li>
    <li>Turrets can get a siphon, buildings with Digging in Deep can be free</li>
    <li>Bunkers to garrison your infantry</li>
    <li>Mantis can move quickly and be invincible thanks to Mech Overcharge</li>
    <li>Still gets Combat Salvage and the EMP mech</li>
    <li>Can be an economic powerhouse - build free gens on many bases once you get Digging in Deep</li>
    <li>Gets really out of hand quickly as the game progresses, like Decimus</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Best Super Turtle combo in twos</strong>: Atriox + Johnson</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Voridus</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Spoils is amazing</strong> - best passive leader power in the game</li>
    <li>Get Combat Spoils 2 and just go attack someone's base</li>
    <li>Can get enough power to buy T2 and T3 - could be T3 in just a handful of minutes on one gen</li>
    <li>If someone is unprepared for Voridus, you'll never catch back up</li>
    <li>One of the most creative leaders with the infusion play style</li>
    <li>Really need to master it to be effective (like Arbiter)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">A Tier (Great Leaders)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Anders</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Ability to spam Sentinels and aggro/destroy bases really quick</li>
    <li>High-risk, high-reward play (takes 3-4 leader points for full Sentinel upgrades)</li>
    <li>Really good with Turtling with Protector Sentinels from Siege</li>
    <li>R&D powers for cheaper unit upgrades</li>
    <li>You know what you're getting: Siege, Sentinels, or fast upgrades</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Arbiter</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Great with Double Arbiter and Decimus - Vortex on someone's base</li>
    <li>Plasma Bolt early with your second point</li>
    <li>Two Plasma Bolts can insta-destroy a Gen or valuable building early game</li>
    <li>Really great with the Phantoms - that's the whole power behind Arbiter</li>
    <li>Hit or miss on performance - one of the more difficult leaders to learn</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Decimus</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Arguably A+ tier between A and S</li>
    <li>Might be a little weaker early, but gets more powerful as game progresses</li>
    <li>Wait too long and Decimus is really hard to stop</li>
    <li>Boundless Fury, Boundless Siphon (works out of combat despite what 343 said)</li>
    <li>Doesn't have any nukes or active heals like many other leaders</li>
    <li>Decimus hero Y ability is like a mini-eradication</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Captain Cutter</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Has so many good unit drops</li>
    <li>Can take nodes faster with Cutters</li>
    <li>ODST drops, close air support (not costing any power)</li>
    <li>OP Cyclops drop</li>
    <li>Very resource-heavy leader with all these drops</li>
    <li>Don't have to train as many units if using all these drops</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Sergeant Forge</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Rolling Economy gets you ahead pretty quick</li>
    <li>Grizzlies might be outplayed by Isabel's Best Defense Scorpions</li>
    <li>Pelican Transport, Heavy Metal, Combat Salvage</li>
    <li>Forge Hero with the Forge Hog is awesome</li>
    <li>Shines on maps like Sentry with Vulture Spam + Heavy Metal + Combat Salvage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Yap Yap the Destroyer</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The Banished version of Cutter in terms of drops</li>
    <li>Gets beam, deployable shield gens, methane party, shade turret drop, grunt mine</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grunt Goblins</strong> - probably the best Y ability of any hero in Halo Wars 2</li>
    <li>Can heal a base, Scarab, or Condor instantly</li>
    <li>One of the most fun leaders for early troll plays with cannon fodder and heavy grunts</li>
    <li>Grunt riders and methane wagons are fun additions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">B Tier (Good Leaders)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Isabel</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Maybe B+ tier</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Ghost in the Machine is completely game-changing</strong> if used correctly</li>
    <li>Holographic Decoy is heavily underrated</li>
    <li>Shares a lot with Forge in the Leader Power Wheel</li>
    <li>Gets Combat Salvage for Vulture Spamming</li>
    <li>Wish she had more unique units - nothing special outside of Best Defense buffing Scorpions and Nightingales</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Jerome</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Like the Mastodon play out of Jerome</li>
    <li>Hero is incredibly expensive (one of the most expensive, up there with Colony)</li>
    <li>Jerome's T1 hero upgrade is the most expensive T1 upgrade out of the gate</li>
    <li>Victory Turret is really good</li>
    <li>Love Omega Team and Enduring Salvo (the Garbage Drop)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Pavium</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>So good at defense, but maybe not the best offensively</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">The Lich is one of the strongest drops in the entire game</strong></li>
    <li>Amazing at taking out units, buildings, bases - plus the bubble ball to build units from</li>
    <li>Love the troll play of Pavium in a bunker or stealing opponent's X-Bow base</li>
    <li>Love Mega Turrets and Rain of Fire on bases</li>
    <li>Pavium hero is way too slow traversing</li>
    <li>Can fall into one dimensional and really fall behind on economy prioritizing Mega Turrets</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">C Tier (Situational)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Serina</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>A little bit better than Kinsano</li>
    <li>Better hero unit with the Ice Cream Truck</li>
    <li>Cryotic Advances is awesome</li>
    <li>Cryo Troopers are more fun to play than Kinsano's Hellbringers</li>
    <li>Kinsano gets Flame Hogs - why can't Serina get Frost Hogs?</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">D Tier (Weakest)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Kinsano</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Just feel like Kinsano is missing something</li>
    <li>Serina gets Cryotic Advances and Frost Siege - how come Kinsano doesn't have Flame Siege?</li>
    <li>Inferno is pretty great</li>
    <li>Kinsano hero Y ability Flame Wall is a troll play</li>
    <li>If you stop the Kinsano hero with Ram Cycling and go anti-vehicle for Flame Hogs, you've figured Kinsano out</li>
    <li>Can do really strong airplay with Redline 2</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Special Mention</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Shipmaster</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Never play Shipmaster.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Key Observations</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Base Leaders vs DLC</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Atriox is really good as a base leader (no DLC required). Out of the six base leaders plus Forge that you get for free, Atriox is really, really good.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Best Passive Abilities</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Voridus Combat Spoils</strong>: Best passive leader power in the game</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Johnson Digging in Deep</strong>: Build free gens on many bases</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Best Hero Y Abilities</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Yap Yap Grunt Goblins</strong>: Probably the best Y ability of any hero - can heal a base, Scarab, or Condor instantly</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Best Leader Combos</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Atriox + Johnson</strong>: Best Super Turtle combo in twos</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Double Arbiter + Decimus</strong>: Vortex debuff + Plasma Bolt can insta-destroy generators early game</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Learning Curve</h3>
  <p class="mb-4"><strong>Arbiter</strong> and <strong>Voridus</strong> are among the more difficult leaders to learn. They have particular play styles that really need to be mastered to be effective.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Here's the complete 2026 tier ranking:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">S Tier:</strong> Atriox, Colony, Johnson, Voridus</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">A Tier:</strong> Anders, Arbiter, Decimus, Captain Cutter, Sergeant Forge, Yap Yap</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">B Tier:</strong> Isabel, Jerome, Pavium</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">C Tier:</strong> Serina</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">D Tier:</strong> Kinsano</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Unranked:</strong> Shipmaster (never play him)</li>
  </ul>

</BlogPostLayout>
